ideas.title: The Yarra's Mystic Depths
ideas.premise: A reporter interviews a Yarra River diver who dramatically claims the lack of news is due to aliens stealing all the stories.
ideas.why_funny: Absurd explanation for no news, referencing the notoriously murky Yarra River.

ideas.title: Tram Stop Propaganda
ideas.premise: A bored commuter vandalizes a tram stop advertisement to make it about the utter lack of anything interesting happening.
ideas.why_funny: Relatable frustration with mundane news, expressed through petty Melbourne rebellion.

ideas.title: Parliamentary Paper Aeroplanes
ideas.premise: Victorian politicians are shown folding newspapers into paper airplanes and throwing them around the empty parliament.
ideas.why_funny: Visual gag highlighting government inactivity due to lack of pressing issues.

ideas.title: The Seagull's Scoop
ideas.premise: A flock of seagulls fights over a single, blank newspaper, symbolizing the news drought.
ideas.why_funny: Seagulls are a common Melbourne sight; the blank newspaper amplifies the joke.

ideas.title: Coffee Crisis Averted
ideas.premise: Headline: 'Melbourne Saved From Coffee Bean Shortage!', but the article is just a photo of a satisfied barista.
ideas.why_funny: Exaggerated relief over a non-issue, playing on Melbourne's coffee obsession.
